      "sourceStatus": "CORRECTION_REQUIRED",
      "sourceText": "Fred W. Hurt, of Fourth and Harvey Streets, gave this version: \"At the first appearance it looked like a comet. I recall Halley's comet and it resembled that. There was, at first, a bright spot ahead of the stream of fire, but the trail didn't look so bright when the object reached its zenith.",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 6,
      "page": 9,
      "pageId": "page_0009",
      "lineId": "page_0009-l0034",
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "sourceStatus": "CORRECTION_REQUIRED",
      "sourceText": "\"It looked like a long black cigar which was on fire\", she stated. \"We heard a faint sound, which might have been a small motor. At times it looked like an airplane 'way, 'way off. I thought at first it might be a comet or a meteor, but it seemed to be traveling too slowly for that. It appeared in the southwest and traveled toward the east. There was a kind of reddish looking smoke about it.\"",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
